2.1.3 Internal Algorithms & Operational Logic
* Workstream Inference Engine (Auto-Routing): When a task arrives without an explicit workstream_id, the service executes a two-stage classification pipeline:
   1. Heuristic & Metadata Filtering: Evaluates explicit routing tags (e.g., [Ollie: WS-123]), Buganizer component mappings, and email sender LDAP against ListenerConfigs.
   2. Semantic Cosine Classification: Computes a 768-dimensional embedding $E_{\text{task}} = \text{Embed}(\text{title} \mathbin{\Vert} \text{description})$ via Vertex AI (textembedding-gecko). Queries active Workstream centroids in Spanner using approximate nearest neighbor search: $$\text{Sim}(E_{\text{task}}, E_{\text{ws}}) = \frac{E_{\text{task}} \cdot E_{\text{ws}}}{|E_{\text{task}}| |E_{\text{ws}}|}$$
   3. Confidence Thresholding:
      * If $\text{Sim} \ge 0.85$, the task is automatically assigned to that workstream and transitions to TRIAGED.
      * If $0.65 \le \text{Sim} < 0.85$, it is placed in the creator's Personal Canvas triage inbox with top candidate recommendations and rationale in TriageTaskResponse.
      * If $\text{Sim} < 0.65$, it defaults to private visibility in the creator's inbox.
* Semantic Duplicate Detection via Vector Similarity: During CreateTask (when skip_duplicate_detection == false), queries open tasks (status NOT IN ('COMPLETED', 'CANCELLED')) within the target workstream using the native Spanner ScaNN vector index:
   * If any existing task exhibits cosine similarity $\ge 0.92$ (distance $\le 0.08$), the engine flags a semantic duplicate.
   * Instead of creating a new row, it automatically calls MergeDuplicateTasks, merging the incoming original_sources array into the existing canonical task, appending a synthesis note to the description, and emitting a DUPLICATE_MERGED event to Feed Service.
* Sub-Task Tree Hierarchy & Cycle Detection: Sub-tasks specify a parent_task_id. To prevent cyclic graph dependencies, CreateSubTask and parent-reassignment updates execute a recursive Common Table Expression (CTE) within a Spanner read-write transaction:


WITH RECURSIVE TaskAncestry AS (
  SELECT task_id, parent_task_id FROM Tasks WHERE workstream_id = @ws_id AND task_id = @parent_id
  UNION ALL
  SELECT t.task_id, t.parent_task_id FROM Tasks t
  JOIN TaskAncestry a ON t.task_id = a.parent_task_id
)
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM TaskAncestry WHERE task_id = @new_child_id;

If count $> 0$, the RPC aborts with INVALID_ARGUMENT: Cyclic task dependency detected. Furthermore, parent completion is conditionally gated: a parent cannot transition to COMPLETED unless $\forall c \in \text{Children}(T), c.\text{status} \in {\text{COMPLETED}, \text{CANCELLED}}$.


