2.2 Task Fulfilment Service
2.2.1 Authoritative Responsibilities & Operational Scope
* Execution Routing & Dispatching: Evaluates task metadata, delegation targets, required tool capabilities, and security boundaries to allocate the optimal runtime execution environment.
* Runtime Lifecycle Supervision: Spawns, monitors, suspends, and terminates agent execution sessions. Enforces dynamic concurrency limits and timeout quotas per workstream tenant.
* Identity Resolution: Enforces strict execution identity boundaries, translating user requests into scoped OAuth session tokens or Workstream Service Account credentials.
