2.3.3 Internal Algorithms & Operational Logic
* Dynamic Relevance Ranking & HITL Pinning: When serving ListFeedCards, applies a dynamic ranking formula to prioritize actionable intelligence over routine log spam: $$\text{Score}(C) = w_1 \cdot \text{Recency}(C) + w_2 \cdot \mathbb{I}(\text{UserMentioned}) + w_3 \cdot \mathbb{I}(\text{HITLRequired}) + w_4 \cdot \text{TaskPriorityWeight}(C)$$ Cards marked with CARD_TYPE_AGENT_QUESTION_HITL and action_status == 'PENDING' receive an overriding weight ($w_3 = 1000.0$), physically pinning them to the top of the timeline until human action is taken.
* Interactive Widget State Machine: Embedded JSON action buttons (e.g., {"action": "APPROVE_CL", "cl_uri": "cl/12345"}) are tracked by action_status. When a user clicks an action widget in the FE, the Feed Service verifies OAuth tokens and directly invokes upstream target RPCs (TaskService.UpdateTask or TaskFulfilmentService.DispatchTaskExecution).


