2.4.3 Internal Algorithms & Operational Logic
* RBAC Evaluation Tree & Identity Delegation: When evaluating AuthorizeAction, queries distributed in-memory caches (backed by Spanner read replicas) for (workstream_id, actor_identity):
   1. Direct Human Lookup: If the actor is a human Gaia ID, permissions are checked against their assigned Role (e.g., ROLE_EDITOR allows ollie.tasks.create, ollie.tasks.update).
   2. Agent Service Account Delegation: If the actor is an automated agent service account (e.g., sobi-actor@...), the gatekeeper resolves the delegating human user who initiated the task execution session. Verifies that the delegating human possesses ROLE_AGENT_DELEGATOR or ROLE_ADMIN, and that the requested tool action falls within the allowed scope of the delegating human's own role.
